Question: I'm in salary band C and my line manager asked me to work several
  hours last Saturday because of a publication deadline. If I take
  payment instead of compensatory leave, how is the amount calculated?
Example answer: For members of staff with a basic salary up to step 59 of salary band
  E, overtime worked on Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays is
  compensated at two hours for each hour of overtime worked. Where
  compensatory leave for overtime cannot be granted, the member of
  staff may instead be granted overtime payment in lieu of leave, and
  the standard hourly rate for such payment is 0.6% of the basic
  monthly salary for the month in which the overtime was worked. (ECB
  Conditions of Employment, page 13; ECB Staff Rules, pages 89–90)
Predicted answer: Short answer (formula): Payment = (0.006 × your basic monthly salary
  for the month when the overtime was worked) × (hours worked on
  Saturday × 2).  What that means in practice - Compute the standard
  hourly cash rate as 0.6% of your basic monthly salary for that month
  (0.006 × monthly salary) (ECB Staff Rules, Art. 5.3.5). - For
  Saturday work you are due 2 compensatory hours for each hour worked.
  If you choose payment, you are paid for those compensatory hours at
  the standard hourly cash rate (ECB Conditions of Employment, p.13).
  - Example: if your basic monthly salary = €5,000 and you worked 3
  hours on Saturday:   - hourly cash rate = 0.006 × €5,000 = €30/hour
  - compensatory hours due = 3 × 2 = 6 hours   - payment = €30 × 6 =
  €180  Other practical rules - Minimum compensable overtime unit: 0.5
  hour (ECB Staff Rules, Art. 5.3.4). - You must submit overtime
  details to DG HR by the 3rd working day of the month following the
  overtime month; payment is made with the monthly salary (ECB Staff
  Rules, Art. 5.3.6). - Overtime payments are subject to tax (ECB
  Staff Rules, Art. 5.3.7). - The Staff Rules allow DG HR, in
  consultation with business-area management, to set maxima for
  weekend hours (no numeric cap was provided in the extracted text)
  (Staff Rules, 5.4bis). - The extracted text does not state further
  rounding conventions for fractional hours; check with DG HR if you
  need a precise rounding rule.  References: ECB Staff Rules, Art.
  5.3.4–5.3.7 and 5.4bis; ECB Conditions of Employment (p.13).    If
  you want, I can compute the exact payment for your case if you tell
  me your basic monthly salary and the number of hours you worked on
  Saturday.
