Question: Following the second consecutive annual review showing
  underperformance, what may happen, and who acts as the second
  reviewer in the annual review process?
Example answer: Where a second consecutive annual review establishes underperformance,
  an underperformance procedure may be initiated. The second reviewer
  is the first reviewer's direct line manager, although upon a
  proposal by the head of the relevant business area, the Director
  General Human Resources or their Deputy (or the Chief Services
  Officer for staff working in DG Human Resources) may decide that
  another staff member shall be the second reviewer or, exceptionally,
  that there shall be no second reviewer. (ECB Staff Rules, pages 48,
  50)
