  underperformance:   - An underperformance procedure may be initiated
  (see Article 8.5, referenced by Article 2a.5.3). Also, when an
  annual review shows underperformance the first reviewer must include
  the elements set out in Article 8.5.2 in the annual review form.  -
  Who acts as the second reviewer:   - By default the second reviewer
  is the first reviewer’s direct line manager. The Director General
  Human Resources (or Deputy), or the Chief Services Officer for staff
  in DG HR, may—on proposal by the head of the business area—appoint a
  different person or, in exceptional cases, decide there is no second
  reviewer. The second reviewer intervenes if there is a disagreement
