  relevant line managers, grants such authorisation if the activity
  does not impair the staff member's professional duties or constitute
  a likely source of conflict of interest, for a maximum of five years
  at a time. Members of staff shall perform external activities
  outside working hours, although on an exceptional basis the Director
  General Human Resources or their Deputy may authorise derogations
  from this rule. (ECB Staff Rules, pages 7–8)
