Question: I want to do a transaction in euro-area government bonds worth EUR
  15,000 in a single month. Do I need authorisation, and from whom,
  and how long before the order should I submit the request?
Example answer: Transactions exceeding EUR 10,000 within any given calendar month in
  government securities issued by euro area Member States are subject
  to prior authorisation by the Compliance and Governance Office. Any
  such request must be submitted at least five working days prior to
  the envisaged order date, and the Office shall decide on the request
  within five working days; if it does not react within five working
  days, the transaction is deemed authorised. (ECB Staff Rules, pages
  15–17)
