Question: If I am suspended pending disciplinary proceedings and part of my
  salary is withheld, when must any withheld amount be reimbursed?
Example answer: If within nine months from the suspension no final decision has been
  taken, or no measure other than a written warning or a written
  reprimand has been adopted, the ECB shall reimburse the member of
  staff the amount of salary withheld. (ECB Conditions of Employment,
  page 23)
