  suspension, no final decision has been taken, or no measure other
  than a written warning or a written reprimand has been adopted, the
  ECB shall reimburse the member of staff the amount of salary
  withheld. Reimbursement is triggered by that nine‑month cut‑off and
  covers the amount withheld from the suspension date (ECB Conditions
  of Employment, Art. 46, p.23).  - Limits and interaction: Any amount
  withheld may not exceed one‑half of the member’s basic salary and
  the member’s income may not be reduced below the minimum subsistence
  figure (Article 35) (ECB Conditions of Employment, Art. 46, p.23).
  - Authority/other consequence: The Executive Board decides on
  suspension and on withholding (with the Chief Services Officer
  acting for staff at salary band I or below under the Staff Rules).
  If the Executive Board (or authorised representative) dismisses a
  member with effect from the day of suspension, the Staff Rules
  indicate different consequences for amounts paid/withheld during
  suspension (amounts paid during suspension are retained by the
  member) (ECB Conditions of Employment, Art. 46, p.23; ECB Staff
  Rules §8.4.1–8.4.2, §8.3.18, pp.128–129).  Sources: ECB Conditions
  of Employment, Art. 46, p.23; ECB Staff Rules §8.4.1–8.4.2, §8.3.18
